Due to COVID-19 safety measures, the First Lady's guests for the President's Address to the Joint Session of Congress will be watching the speech remotely. However, at 4:00 PM EST on April 28, Dr. Jill Biden will host a virtual reception with this year's guests. The guests include Javier Quiroz Castro, a Dreamer, DACA recipient, and nurse; Maria-Isabel Ballivian, the Executive Director of the ACCA Child Development Center; Tatiana Washington, a gun violence prevention advocate and organizer; Stella Keating, the first transgender teenager to testify before the U.S. Senate; and Theron Rutyna, the IT Director for the Red Cliff Band of Lake Superior Chippewa. Each guest represents issues or policies that will be addressed by the President in his speech.